The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 19: The government may sell a 10 per cent stake in profit-making public sector unit Bhel, heavy industries minister Vilasrao Deshmukh said. The point of divestment is still under consideration. The government has definitely a positive thinking on that line, he said.                            
	 Calcutta, June 19: GM India will continue to roll out models under the Chevrolet brand in India. However, the US auto maker will not introduce cars in other platforms. We will continue to roll out newer models from the Chevrolet platform, GM India president and MD Karl Slym said.                            
	 New Delhi, June 19: The government today allowed realty major K Raheja Universal to opt out of two special economic zones at Navi Mumbai. It also gave a go-ahead to the metro passage through DLF SEZ in Gurgaon.                            
	 New Delhi, June 19: Tata Steel has raised prices of its products by up to Rs 750 a tonne because of improved domestic demand and a firming global trend. Prices of hot and cold-rolled steel items have been raised by Rs 500-750 a tonne on monthly contracts in select regions.                            
	 Calcutta, June 19: Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd (BSNL) today officially launched the Internet-protocal TV or IPTV service in Calcutta and Bengal to take on the DTH players.                                                                                                                           
